{ "type": "Feature", "properties": { "Name": "Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage", "Descriptio": "The Annaram Barrage, officially known as the Saraswathi Barrage, is a monumental hydraulic structure built across the Godavari River in Telangana, India. \nAs a critical component of the ambitious Kaleshwaram Lift Irrigation Scheme (KLIS), it is designed to turn the arid regions of Telangana into fertile, productive agricultural land. Situated in the Jayashankar Bhupalpally district, this engineering marvel is a testament to the state’s commitment to water conservation and agricultural rejuvenation. \nThe barrage not only plays a vital role in providing irrigation but also serves as a crucial infrastructure point, offering scenic views and connecting different parts of the region. The Saraswathi Barrage is located near Annaram village in the Mahadevpur Mandal of the Jayashankar Bhupalpally district. \nIt is part of the second of three planned barrages in the KLIS project, sitting strategically to manage the flow of the Godavari River.", "Country": "India", "Photos": "images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage.png|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage1.png|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage2.png|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage3.png|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage4.jfif|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage5.jfif|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage6.PNG|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage7.PNG|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage8.PNG|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage9.PNG|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage10.PNG|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage11.PNG|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage12.PNG|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage13.PNG|images\\Annaram\\Annaram(Saraswathi) Barrage14.PNG", "State": "Telangana" }, "geometry": { "type": "Point", "coordinates": [ 79.824019074740733, 18.76357209544511 ] } },
